Parity

David Smith

2022-11-02

\(\uparrow\) Library - Hub || Mosquito

History of the idea:

  • In 1952, Macdonalds analysis of the sporozoite rate caused a revolution in malaria epidemiology [1].

  • In the next two years, parity was the subject of two nature papers: Draper and Davidson proposed a method for estimating the survival rate of mosquitoes using parity [2]; and [3]

  • In 1954, Gillies described the use of the pre-gravid rate and the sporozoite rate as a way of estimating the age structure of a population [4].

Models

Deterministic

This one is easy to analyze:

\[\begin{equation}\begin{array}{rl} \dot M &= \Lambda(t)- g M \\ \dot P &= f(M-P) - g P \end{array}\end{equation}\]

This one is easier to add noise:
\[\begin{equation}\begin{array}{rl} M_{t+1} &= \Lambda_t + p M_t \\ P_{t+1} &= f_t (M_t - P_t) + p P_t \end{array}\end{equation}\]

deltaMP = function(t, vars, pars){with(as.list(c(vars,pars)), {
  Mt = Lambda*(1.1+sin(2*pi*t/365)) - g*M
  Pt = f*(M-P)  - g*P
  c(M=Mt, P=Pt)
})}
inits = c(M=0, P=0)
params = c(f=.3, g=1/10, Lambda=10)
MP = inits 
for(t in 355:365) MP = deltaMP(t, MP, params)
MPt = MP

for(t in 1:730){
  MP = deltaMP(t, MP, params)
  MPt = rbind(MPt, MP) 
}
MPt = data.frame(MPt)
MPt$t = 0:730
MPt$np = 1-MPt$P/(MPt$M+MPt$P)
MPt$U = (MPt$M-MPt$P)
par(mfrow = c(2,1))

plot(MPt$t, MPt$M, type = "l", ylim = range(0, MPt$M), ylab = "Population Densities", col = grey(0.5))
lines(MPt$t, MPt$U, col = "blue")  
lines(MPt$t, MPt$P, col = "red") 

plot(MPt$t, MPt$np, type = "l", ylab ="Fraction Null-Parous")

Stochastic

deltaUPs = function(t, vars, pars){with(as.list(c(vars,pars)), {
  Pt = ifelse(P>0, rbinom(1, P, p),0) 
  Ut = ifelse(U>0, rbinom(1, U, p),0) 
  emerged = rnbinom(1, mu=Lambda*(1.1+sin(2*pi*t/365)), size=sz) 
  fed = ifelse(Ut>0, rbinom(1,Ut,f),0)
  Ut = Ut-fed+emerged
  Pt = Pt+fed
  if(is.null(Pt)) browser()
  if(is.null(Ut)) browser()
  c(U=Ut, P=Pt)
})}
inits = c(U=100, P=10)
params = c(f=.3, p=.9, Lambda=10, sz=.1)
UP = inits 
for(t in 355:365) UP = deltaUPs(t, UP, params)

MPt = UP
for(t in 1:730){
  UP = deltaUPs(t, UP, params)
  MPt = rbind(MPt, UP) 
}
MPt = data.frame(MPt)
MPt$t = 0:730
MPt$np = MPt$U/(MPt$U+MPt$P)
MPt$M = (MPt$U+MPt$P)
par(mfrow = c(2,1))
tm = 0:730
plot(MPt$t, MPt$M, type = "l", ylim = range(0, MPt), ylab = "Population Densities", col = grey(0.5))
lines(MPt$t, MPt$U, col = "blue")  
lines(MPt$t, MPt$P, col = "red") 

plot(MPt$t, MPt$np, type = "l", ylab ="Fraction Null-Parous")
